flowRoot.flowPara: An Exploration into Neural Architectures for Learning to Play Pacman.
Pacman provides a sophisticated challenge for machine learning given the number of possible states a game can be in.
Therefore without the availability of a supercomputer a prediction engine becomes the necessary means.
This research aims to explore and evaluate various neural network architectures in order to learn and play Pacman.

We are currently implementing all architectures and do not have any conclusive results at the current time. Our initial findings show that Pacman performs better utilising Q-Learning than Valid Random and Valid Random with Momentum.
CNNs appear to produce superior results even with simple architectures though results are not yet conclusive.
